HEADWORD: Skilling
<hw>Skil"ling</hw> <pr>(sk⟦icr⟧l"l⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Sheeling</er>.]</ety> <def>A bay of a barn; also, a slight addition
to a cottage.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skilling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Skilling
<hw>Skil"ling</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sw. & Dan. See
<er>Shilling</er>.]</ety> <def>A money of account in Sweden, Norway,
Denmark, and North Germany, and also a coin. It had various values, from
three fourths of a cent in Norway to more than two cents in
L⟦uum⟧beck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skill-less</ent>⟦br⟧
